description: The North American F-86F-2 Sabre is a single-engined, swept-wing, fighter-bomber. The F-86F-2 is derived from the F-86F-1, but with four T-160 20-mm guns in place of the .50-cal guns. These were fitted as part of the GUNVAL trials to find a more effective armament for USAF fighters. The F-86F-2 has the 6-3 wing.
